    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - REMOVE - REAR AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR AND YOKE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REAR AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR AND YOKE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut the lockwire on the splitter yoke retaining bolt (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301936">Figure 36</hotlnk>) and loosen the bolt (inset).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301936" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301936" filename="../figg13/g1301936.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Cut Lockwire on Splitter Yoke Retaining Bolt and Loosen Bolt</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolt, splitter yoke and sliding clutch assembly from the auxiliary
                section (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301937">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301937" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301937" filename="../figg13/g1301937.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Remove Retaining Bolt, Splitter Yoke and Sliding Clutch Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
